27/03/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The IMF Board approved on Friday (March 25th) the seventh and last review of a stand-by agreement with Romania.
According to Mihai Tanasescu, the country's representative within the Fund, the board found Romania has met its commitments.
Romania has received 11.3 billion euros so far from the IMF as part of a 20 billion-euro financial aid package provided in 2009.
The new precautionary deal aims at maintaining fiscal discipline and the continuation of structural reforms.
(Agerpres, Mediafax, Hotnews.ro - 25/03/11)
